summary: A custom meshed player cabin near Halfmoon Mill, obtained through a short quest.
descriptionHtml:
**Update* New adjustments have been made. Version 1.1 is being uploaded currently. This version combines patches for increased performance and stability. Currently I have not crashed using this mod on a vanilla game running all DLCs with the Dawnguard Required version enabled through testing though I will look out for bugs if reported. A \"Main\" file has been uploaded that should work for all mid range systems, feel free to download the optional texture size versions for your system if you see fit.

Custom meshed player home with over 120 custom objects. This is currently in late WIP phase / testing phase and may require bug fixes or updates. House includes the following areas. I am not an expert in modeling or texture though I am learning, I thought it would be beneficial to create a mod as part of that process. I hope you guys enjoy it.

Texture sizes in case anyone is wondering: 512 is the smallest download with performance in mind over quality. 4096 is the largest size with looks in mind, but has an impact on performance. I can currently run the house on a phenom 2 x4 965 with an ATI radeon 5850 1GB at high with half a bar on object draw distance in game without many issues, just to give people an idea.

If you try running a texture size or settings too high for your game, you may experience random crashing due to texture size requirements being too high for some peoples graphics cards.

This house requires a key to unlock. The key can be acquired through hints placed near the front of the home when first arriving. You can also view the readme if you don\'t mind spoilers - though it is a simple and straight forward way of obtaining the home. I\'m a newbie at scripting - I won\'t be able to provide an interesting quest for this mod at the moment.

Bath
Dining area
Flora area
Guest room
Main bedroom
Basement
Crafting area
Bar
Dock
Outside deck

Some items are being worked on, though the cabin is mostly finished. I\'m still checking out for or troubleshooting possible issues with weapon racks.
----------------------------------------------------------------

Currently Planned updates

*Fix weapon rack bug
*Test out Hearthfire and Dragonborn DLCs to ensure no errors or crashes.
